<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<script is:inline>
			(() => {
				try {
					const theme = localStorage.getItem("theme");
					if (theme === "dark" || theme === "light") {
						document.documentElement.dataset.theme = theme;
					}
				} catch {}
			})();
		</script>
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/global.css" />
		<title>Nazare</title>
		<meta
			name="description"
			content="Nazare is an easy-to-maintain and easy-to-update Liquid toolkit."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<header class="site-header">
			<a href="/" aria-label="Nazare home">Nazare</a>
			<nav aria-label="Primary navigation">
				<a href="https://github.com/fedorivanenko/nazare">GitHub</a>
			</nav>
		</header>
		<main class="site-shell stack">
			<button
				class="theme-toggle"
				type="button"
				onclick="setTheme(document.documentElement.dataset.theme === 'dark' ? 'light' : 'dark')"
			>
				Toggle theme
			</button>
			<section class="stack">
				<h1 class="heading">Easy-to-maintain and easy-to-update Liquid in one toolkit.</h1>
				<p class="muted">
					Nazare brings type safety, reusable components, and whole-repo intelligence to
					Shopify Liquid — without forcing you into a complex headless architecture.
				</p>
				<p>
					Nazare is incrementally adoptable. Start with individual pieces like the
					registry or types for your current Liquid theme, or adopt the full stack.
				</p>
				<div>
					<a href="https://github.com/fedorivanenko/nazare">View source</a>
				</div>
			</section>
			<section class="card stack">
				<h2 class="heading">Right Now</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>
						Install editable, styleless components from an open-source registry inspired
						by shadcn/ui.
					</li>
					<li>
						Get strong type-checking with clear validation errors, React-style
						composition, and forget about prop drilling with a TS-inspired superset.
					</li>
					<li>
						Organize source code in a developer-friendly, monorepo-style workspace while
						compiling to a standard Shopify theme.
					</li>
					<li>
						Have full support of your current Liquid theme with extra validation and
						protection layer.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</section>
			<section class="card stack">
				<h2 class="heading">Soon</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>
						Deduplicate and minify CSS with an integrated pipeline and first-class
						Tailwind support.
					</li>
					<li>
						Control load strategies and hydration with a tiny JS island framework, or
						bring any JS you want.
					</li>
					<li>
						Get a hosted Storybook-style environment for browsing, testing, and
						documenting components.
					</li>
					<li>Validate templates against typed storefront data before deployment.</li>
					<li>
						Give AI agents an explicit model of your theme and storefront so they can
						understand and modify your codebase far more reliably.
					</li>
					<li>
						Run A/B tests and personalize your storefront without bringing complex
						headless solutions.
					</li>
				</ul>
				<p>Plus LSP, dev server, theme-check iterations, and more.</p>
			</section>
		</main>
		<script is:inline>
			window.setTheme = (theme) => {
				document.documentElement.dataset.theme = theme;
				localStorage.setItem("theme", theme);
			};
		</script>
	</body>
</html>
